1
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:36,911
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:01:00,059 --> 00:01:01,060
Hold on.

3
00:01:03,312 --> 00:01:04,313
Well, here we are.

4
00:01:05,106 --> 00:01:07,024
I'll head in now. Get home safely.

5
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:09,485
I still have something to tell you.

6
00:01:09,652 --> 00:01:11,070
Oh, what is it?

7
00:01:12,905 --> 00:01:14,865
You know how you told me
to stand for what I love?

8
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:16,576
I like you.

9
00:01:19,745 --> 00:01:22,748
- Huh?
- I know I'm not that great right now.

10
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:25,042
But I'm going to take acting seriously.

11
00:01:25,376 --> 00:01:28,421
I have an audition booked,
and I'll keep trying until I get hired.

12
00:01:31,716 --> 00:01:34,010
- Ji-su...
- I'll dress well around you

13
00:01:34,635 --> 00:01:36,887
so that I don't embarrass you.

14
00:01:37,138 --> 00:01:40,266
I'll also move to a nice place
where you can come visit.

15
00:01:41,225 --> 00:01:43,394
I can't take you
to a fancy restaurant often

16
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:45,771
but I promise to take you to one

17
00:01:46,897 --> 00:01:47,898
for big celebrations.

18
00:01:50,776 --> 00:01:51,819
I want...

19
00:01:54,572 --> 00:01:55,823
to fall in love with you.

20
00:02:02,747 --> 00:02:04,081
Oh, I...

21
00:02:08,628 --> 00:02:09,754
Tae-seop.

22
00:02:14,925 --> 00:02:16,260
What do you think you're doing?

23
00:02:16,344 --> 00:02:18,679
Whatever I'm doing,
it's none of your business.

24
00:02:18,763 --> 00:02:19,764
Is it really not?

25
00:02:19,847 --> 00:02:22,433
You know Ui-yeong and I have feelings
for each other.

26
00:02:23,225 --> 00:02:24,644
As I told you at the hotel

27
00:02:24,852 --> 00:02:28,105
I don't like
seeing you hanging around her.

28
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:31,692
Yeah, I remember that.

29
00:02:33,235 --> 00:02:34,695
But I like her, too.

30
00:02:35,404 --> 00:02:37,698
I'm not in a place to care
about how you feel

31
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:39,408
or back down for you.

32
00:02:42,244 --> 00:02:44,330
Tae-seop...

33
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:46,999
You three!

34
00:02:47,958 --> 00:02:49,669
Hello.

35
00:02:49,752 --> 00:02:51,796
What are you doing out so late?

36
00:02:51,879 --> 00:02:54,507
Your face looks pale, young lady.

37
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:56,509
Are they bothering you?

38
00:02:56,592 --> 00:02:58,177
- No.
- Should I call the cops?

39
00:02:58,260 --> 00:02:59,512
It's nothing like that.

40
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:03,265
I was just heading inside.

41
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:05,810
Okay, goodnight.

42
00:03:07,853 --> 00:03:09,605
She can answer us separately.

43
00:03:11,273 --> 00:03:12,608
Sorry, Ui-yeong.

44
00:03:13,275 --> 00:03:14,652
You'd better head in.

45
00:03:14,735 --> 00:03:17,530
Goodnight, then.

46
00:03:17,988 --> 00:03:18,989
Bye.

47
00:03:23,035 --> 00:03:24,036
Ui-yeong!

48
00:03:24,912 --> 00:03:27,081
Think about what I said, okay?

49
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:45,975
Aren't you leaving?

50
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:53,899
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 8

51
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:55,651
I'm home.

52
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:57,027
Hey.

53
00:03:57,570 --> 00:03:58,738
Did you just get off work?

54
00:03:59,071 --> 00:04:01,365
No, I met up with a friend after work.

55
00:04:02,116 --> 00:04:03,117
Who? Seung-jun?

56
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:05,327
You seem exhausted.
Did you work out with him?

57
00:04:06,662 --> 00:04:09,790
You know what? I'm tired.
I'm going to bed. Goodnight.

58
00:04:10,374 --> 00:04:11,375
Sure.

59
00:04:22,303 --> 00:04:23,888
Who would possibly imagine

60
00:04:24,263 --> 00:04:26,682
blind dates would lead to such a mess?

61
00:04:51,874 --> 00:04:54,043
I should've asked her out sooner

62
00:04:54,835 --> 00:04:56,670
but I let some other guy beat me to it.

63
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:37,002
I've never felt this way before.

64
00:05:40,005 --> 00:05:41,507
That wouldn't mean anything to her.

65
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:46,512
I'm following my heart

66
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:49,390
instead of my logic...

67
00:05:57,439 --> 00:06:01,235
Yeah, if I keep trying,
there will be a chance.

68
00:06:07,241 --> 00:06:10,202
You'll have much more fun with me
than with that guy.

69
00:06:32,349 --> 00:06:33,809
Gosh, what do I do?

70
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:01,587
We're running out of the amenity supplies.

71
00:07:01,670 --> 00:07:03,422
We'll need to order some more.

72
00:07:03,505 --> 00:07:05,799
The Recycling Act came into effect
years ago

73
00:07:05,883 --> 00:07:07,801
and we're finally out
of single-use amenities.

74
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:10,721
Other hotels went from single-use
to refillables in steps, right?

75
00:07:10,804 --> 00:07:13,265
Yeah, some have started selling
single-use amenities

76
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:15,559
for anywhere from 1,000 to 2,000 won.

77
00:07:15,643 --> 00:07:19,355
Others are selling
eco-friendly or quality ones for higher.

78
00:07:19,438 --> 00:07:22,608
What do you think would be better,
Ms. Lee?

79
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:25,486
Ms. Lee?

80
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:27,112
Ms. Lee?

81
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,990
Oh, what? Yeah.

82
00:07:30,824 --> 00:07:32,910
Oh, well

83
00:07:33,202 --> 00:07:35,412
it depends on whether we see amenities

84
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:38,916
as a service or profitable goods.

85
00:07:38,999 --> 00:07:41,543
I think they should be considered
service products.

86
00:07:41,627 --> 00:07:43,170
You think so? Why?

87
00:07:43,253 --> 00:07:46,715
Our guests would feel inconvenienced
and dissatisfied without them

88
00:07:46,799 --> 00:07:48,592
leading them to think

89
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:51,261
the quality of our hotel's service
has gone down.

90
00:07:51,929 --> 00:07:52,930
You're right.

91
00:07:53,889 --> 00:07:54,890
So, what should we do?

92
00:07:55,182 --> 00:07:56,558
Let's see. What should we do?

93
00:08:01,021 --> 00:08:02,439
You're really incredible.

94
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:05,484
How can you zone out
and snap out of it just like that?

95
00:08:06,652 --> 00:08:07,695
Was it obvious?

96
00:08:09,196 --> 00:08:11,824
It's so easy to talk
about work-related things

97
00:08:12,199 --> 00:08:15,452
but why is it that the more I think,
the more confused I get about feelings?

98
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:18,831
You need some fresh air? Or some coffee?

99
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:20,791
Yeah, some coffee would...

100
00:08:21,750 --> 00:08:24,712
No, I'll pass on coffee today.

101
00:08:24,795 --> 00:08:27,089
You can go and get some.
I'll clean up here.

102
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:32,720
Thank you.

103
00:08:33,095 --> 00:08:34,096
"Lee Ui-yeong"?

104
00:08:35,931 --> 00:08:38,934
Ui-yeong, this was delivered to you.

105
00:08:39,184 --> 00:08:41,770
Mr. Song ordered it for you.

106
00:08:42,312 --> 00:08:44,273
- I'll take one.
- Sure.

107
00:08:44,356 --> 00:08:48,027
When did you two become close enough
to get coffee for each other?

108
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:53,240
Ui-yeong,
the air pollution level is high today.

109
00:08:53,323 --> 00:08:54,992
Going out wouldn't be a good idea.

110
00:08:55,075 --> 00:08:56,201
Have a great day!

111
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:57,494
Look, Ui-yeong!

112
00:08:57,661 --> 00:08:58,787
Huh? Coffee?

113
00:08:58,871 --> 00:09:00,789
What? Why do you have so much coffee?

114
00:09:01,790 --> 00:09:03,917
Ji-su told me to bring these
to the whole team.

115
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:06,253
And he said

116
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:08,589
"You'd better not get coffee elsewhere.

117
00:09:08,672 --> 00:09:10,674
If you don't come see me,
I'll come see you."

118
00:09:10,966 --> 00:09:12,176
He told me to tell you that.

119
00:09:12,634 --> 00:09:14,803
What? That's odd.

120
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:18,140
Why is everyone competing
to buy coffee for Ui-yeong?

121
00:09:18,682 --> 00:09:20,309
What's weird about that?

122
00:09:20,726 --> 00:09:21,935
It's just coffee.

123
00:09:22,394 --> 00:09:24,354
It's just a coincidence.

124
00:09:24,438 --> 00:09:25,689
It's great for us.

125
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:28,358
It's like a coffee party!

126
00:09:28,442 --> 00:09:30,027
It's a party!

127
00:09:37,534 --> 00:09:39,912
I'd hoped
it'd be just a one-time coincidence...

128
00:09:40,204 --> 00:09:41,705
- Here for a meeting?
- Yeah.

129
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:44,416
But that coffee incident was
the start of a long battle.

130
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:45,793
Hey, your shirt is unbuttoned.

131
00:09:46,001 --> 00:09:47,211
I unbuttoned it for you.

132
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:50,339
A man trying to change my mind.

133
00:09:51,715 --> 00:09:53,092
That's hot!

134
00:09:54,635 --> 00:09:55,636
Huh?

135
00:09:57,805 --> 00:09:59,223
Alright, I'm off!

136
00:09:59,932 --> 00:10:01,850
- Enjoy your date!
- Bye.

137
00:10:02,226 --> 00:10:03,268
Tae-seop.

138
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:05,479
I thought I'd give you a lift home
on the way.

139
00:10:05,896 --> 00:10:06,939
Are you hungry?

140
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:08,565
No, not yet.

141
00:10:08,649 --> 00:10:11,026
And a man determined to keep me.

142
00:10:12,152 --> 00:10:13,237
SONG TAE-SEOP

143
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,530
Are you at work now?

144
00:10:14,613 --> 00:10:17,574
Seeing the blue sky this morning
made me so happy.

145
00:10:17,783 --> 00:10:20,327
I know you're busy,
but don't forget to look at the sky

146
00:10:20,410 --> 00:10:21,620
and have a good day!

147
00:10:23,163 --> 00:10:26,291
I feel like I just got to work,
but it's already lunchtime.

148
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,210
Don't skip lunch just because you're busy.

149
00:10:28,293 --> 00:10:30,838
And eat slowly so you don't get heartburn.

150
00:10:31,213 --> 00:10:32,506
Have a good afternoon!

151
00:10:34,216 --> 00:10:39,138
HAVE A GOOD AFTERNOON!

152
00:10:40,347 --> 00:10:43,642
A man who's diligent,
even when it comes to flirting.

153
00:10:46,395 --> 00:10:47,896
UI-YEONG! WHAT ARE YOU DOING? YOU BUSY?

154
00:10:48,355 --> 00:10:51,024
You must've had lunch by now.
Don't you want some coffee?

155
00:10:51,275 --> 00:10:53,277
I'll make a latte for you, your favorite.

156
00:10:53,527 --> 00:10:54,528
Come for some coffee.

157
00:10:54,736 --> 00:10:57,739
And a man who just flirts with me
whenever and wherever.

158
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,041
Your drink is ready.

159
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:53,712
Ui-yeong!

160
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:57,007
Hey!

161
00:12:13,857 --> 00:12:15,859
You came a long way for nothing.

162
00:12:16,151 --> 00:12:17,236
I feel bad for you.

163
00:12:17,694 --> 00:12:19,780
Efficiency doesn't matter
when I do what I love.

164
00:12:19,988 --> 00:12:22,783
And we'll have to see
if this was really for nothing.

165
00:12:23,992 --> 00:12:26,203
Sure, then. Go on.

166
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:36,129
A mother-in-law who runs
your favorite restaurant

167
00:12:36,213 --> 00:12:37,881
or a celebrity mother-in-law?

168
00:12:37,965 --> 00:12:40,259
Cut it out.
"This or That" should be banned.

169
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:43,011
I'm not even close
to leaning toward one over the other.

170
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:45,847
This game just exhausts me.
Don't even start.

171
00:12:46,431 --> 00:12:48,809
I've never seen a player in such a dilemma

172
00:12:48,892 --> 00:12:50,936
with both options in her hands.

173
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:53,230
I guess it takes talent to be a player.

174
00:12:53,438 --> 00:12:54,439
Playing men...

175
00:12:55,899 --> 00:12:58,694
It's so complicated and disrespectful.
Why do people do it?

176
00:13:00,362 --> 00:13:01,780
You tell me.

177
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:04,241
How can we understand
the hearts of players

178
00:13:04,324 --> 00:13:06,368
when we're only ever being played?

179
00:13:08,245 --> 00:13:10,205
What do you mean by "we"?

180
00:13:11,707 --> 00:13:12,791
None of your business.

181
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:16,253
Anyway, maybe it's better
that those guys are being played by you.

182
00:13:16,336 --> 00:13:19,298
I might be being played by someone
who has a flock of fish.

183
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:21,049
You mean "school of fish," you idiot.

184
00:13:24,344 --> 00:13:25,679
My stomach hurts.

185
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:28,849
Why do you eat spicy food
when you know it'll hurt?

186
00:13:33,312 --> 00:13:35,022
I miss Songi Spicy Chicken Feet so much.

187
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:37,983
It was just spicy enough
to relieve my stress.

188
00:13:38,650 --> 00:13:40,902
It doesn't compare to this capsaicin mess.

189
00:13:41,611 --> 00:13:43,655
Hey, you don't think his mother

190
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:45,991
no, the owner

191
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:49,286
is waiting for us, disappointed
that we haven't gone recently, right?

192
00:13:49,369 --> 00:13:52,372
How can you be worrying
about your favorite spot somewhere else?

193
00:13:52,456 --> 00:13:54,499
You're too soft.

194
00:13:54,583 --> 00:13:57,711
That's why men keep throwing
new dilemmas at you daily.

195
00:13:57,836 --> 00:13:59,796
Man, you think so?

196
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:01,882
Stop falling for those unimpressive tricks

197
00:14:02,382 --> 00:14:03,675
and choose the stronger one!

198
00:14:04,718 --> 00:14:06,470
- Who has bigger thighs?
- What?

199
00:14:06,553 --> 00:14:08,347
It doesn't seem like a big deal, but...

200
00:14:08,430 --> 00:14:11,725
You want me to measure their thighs?
Or make them wrestle to test it?

201
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:13,393
If it comes down to it, yeah.

202
00:14:13,477 --> 00:14:16,521
I'm sure they'll gladly participate.
They want this to be over, too.

203
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:19,941
And you have to get your head in the game.

204
00:14:21,735 --> 00:14:22,736
Fine.

205
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:27,824
Let's get going.

206
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:29,826
I have to head back to teach.

207
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:31,203
Okay, let's go.

208
00:14:33,121 --> 00:14:35,624
Seung-jun! When do you get off work today?

209
00:14:35,707 --> 00:14:37,000
Can I go to the gym?

210
00:14:37,084 --> 00:14:38,960
I have to be in the area, anyway.

211
00:14:41,421 --> 00:14:42,422
Let's go!

212
00:14:47,302 --> 00:14:48,804
I was wondering where I saw her

213
00:14:49,971 --> 00:14:51,014
but I remembered

214
00:14:51,473 --> 00:14:53,141
that I met her on a dating app.

215
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:56,103
She said she loved my sexy forearms.

216
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:04,486
Seung-jun!

217
00:15:07,531 --> 00:15:09,116
Why didn't you text me first?

218
00:15:09,449 --> 00:15:10,492
I did.

219
00:15:10,867 --> 00:15:12,828
You were just too busy
to check your phone.

220
00:15:14,287 --> 00:15:17,249
Oh, yeah. I don't check my phone
while working.

221
00:15:17,958 --> 00:15:20,001
Which is why I'm here!

222
00:15:20,710 --> 00:15:24,131
I can work out while I wait, right?
You offer day passes?

223
00:15:24,756 --> 00:15:26,383
Yeah, I do.

224
00:15:26,675 --> 00:15:28,176
But the gym's full today.

225
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,804
- You can wait at the cafe...
- Oh! Ms. Cooler!

226
00:15:30,887 --> 00:15:32,139
That's me!

227
00:15:32,222 --> 00:15:34,224
- Would you like a day pass?
- Yes, please.

228
00:15:34,307 --> 00:15:36,935
We'll give you a special discount
since you're special to us.

229
00:15:37,018 --> 00:15:38,186
Thank you!

230
00:15:40,897 --> 00:15:43,608
You should just register at our gym.
You'd brighten it up.

231
00:15:43,733 --> 00:15:44,818
- Should I?
- Hey

232
00:15:44,943 --> 00:15:46,653
who told you to get more business?

233
00:15:50,198 --> 00:15:51,199
What?

234
00:15:52,659 --> 00:15:55,704
I could use this as a blanket
when I go to bed.

235
00:15:55,787 --> 00:15:56,788
It's so big.

236
00:15:57,998 --> 00:15:59,958
You need to trap the heat to warm up.

237
00:16:01,126 --> 00:16:03,170
First, go on the elliptical
for 30 minutes.

238
00:16:04,254 --> 00:16:05,881
No, I'm here to lift weights.

239
00:16:05,964 --> 00:16:08,967
I walked 20 minutes here for cardio
so that I could get right to that.

240
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:11,803
Are you an expert? No, I am!

241
00:16:14,139 --> 00:16:16,099
I really hate doing cardio, though.

242
00:16:17,142 --> 00:16:19,019
Come on. Go and get changed.

243
00:16:37,245 --> 00:16:38,788
Are you coming from the restaurant?

244
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:41,291
Yeah, your mom babysat Sua.

245
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:43,793
I would've gone with you
if I knew you'd be off so soon.

246
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:47,506
Your mom seems curious
about how things are going

247
00:16:47,964 --> 00:16:49,299
with Ui-yeong.

248
00:16:49,382 --> 00:16:52,636
I went to see her, but I barely did.

249
00:16:52,928 --> 00:16:54,471
I only saw someone I didn't want to.

250
00:16:56,014 --> 00:16:57,390
- That barista?
- Yeah.

251
00:16:57,474 --> 00:16:58,517
Man!

252
00:16:59,142 --> 00:17:00,685
Sua, get your tools.

253
00:17:01,019 --> 00:17:02,354
Time to put him in his place.

254
00:17:03,980 --> 00:17:05,690
I got dragged into a mess.

255
00:17:05,774 --> 00:17:07,400
All I did was fall for someone.

256
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:09,027
I wasn't in it for a fight.

257
00:17:11,238 --> 00:17:12,906
This will make you happier. Go!

258
00:17:13,615 --> 00:17:15,408
- Hmm?
- Whatever you do

259
00:17:15,492 --> 00:17:16,785
just be yourself.

260
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:24,960
Be myself...

261
00:17:30,048 --> 00:17:31,925
I shouldn't have had that tteokbokki.

262
00:17:33,677 --> 00:17:35,053
- Mom.
- Yeah?

263
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:37,264
Do we have meds for heartburn?

264
00:17:39,349 --> 00:17:41,017
Not if there's none there.

265
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:42,602
Is it really bad?

266
00:17:42,686 --> 00:17:43,937
Yeah, it's pretty bad.

267
00:17:45,063 --> 00:17:46,231
There's nothing.

268
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:49,192
I'm going to lay in bed for a bit.

269
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:52,904
You sure you'll be okay?

270
00:17:52,988 --> 00:17:53,989
Yeah.

271
00:18:06,626 --> 00:18:09,087
Did you have dinner, Ui-yeong?

272
00:18:11,298 --> 00:18:13,341
Yeah, I ate out before coming home.

273
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:17,095
I'm just in bed right now
because I have heartburn.

274
00:18:22,767 --> 00:18:23,977
Hey, Tae-seop.

275
00:18:24,060 --> 00:18:25,395
Can you talk?

276
00:18:25,645 --> 00:18:27,439
How does it hurt?

277
00:18:27,522 --> 00:18:29,649
Oh, it's nothing serious.

278
00:18:30,066 --> 00:18:33,153
My stomach's been upset lately,
and I had spicy food for dinner.

279
00:18:33,236 --> 00:18:34,696
Do you have meds?

280
00:18:35,196 --> 00:18:36,698
We ran out.

281
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:40,118
But I'll be fine if I get some sleep.

282
00:18:41,161 --> 00:18:44,539
It's hard to sleep when you're in pain.
Hold on.

283
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:49,002
Hello? Tae-seop?

284
00:18:50,879 --> 00:18:52,005
Did it just disconnect?

285
00:19:04,726 --> 00:19:05,769
Hey, Ui-yeong.

286
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:07,312
Tae-seop.

287
00:19:08,271 --> 00:19:09,814
I got some chamomile tea for you.

288
00:19:09,898 --> 00:19:12,025
Oh, thanks.

289
00:19:12,942 --> 00:19:15,403
Did you come all the way to give me meds?

290
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:16,946
Yeah.

291
00:19:17,989 --> 00:19:18,990
Thanks.

292
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:20,408
It's nothing.

293
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:25,497
The air's so fresh.

294
00:19:27,582 --> 00:19:29,751
It would've been perfect
if we had some ice cream.

295
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:33,588
I do that pretty often with my mom
after taking out recycling.

296
00:19:34,923 --> 00:19:37,217
Is your stomach better?

297
00:19:38,009 --> 00:19:39,469
Oh, you're right.

298
00:19:40,345 --> 00:19:41,846
It's all thanks to you.

299
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:45,392
Stomach pains come from stress.

300
00:19:45,475 --> 00:19:47,602
It seems like I caused the pain
and made it better.

301
00:19:47,977 --> 00:19:49,688
No, it's not like that.

302
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:53,983
I know, but I couldn't stop
thinking about you, so here I am.

303
00:20:02,117 --> 00:20:03,118
I...

304
00:20:04,536 --> 00:20:05,912
like you.

305
00:20:08,957 --> 00:20:12,085
They say you have to make up your mind
by the third date.

306
00:20:12,961 --> 00:20:15,171
I wasn't sure if I could feel anything
in three dates

307
00:20:16,089 --> 00:20:17,090
but I did.

308
00:20:19,426 --> 00:20:20,468
But...

309
00:20:21,010 --> 00:20:22,721
I've been too anxious lately

310
00:20:22,971 --> 00:20:24,806
I forgot to be mindful of your feelings.

311
00:20:26,641 --> 00:20:29,561
I'm not sure if I deserve to be respected
right now.

312
00:20:30,186 --> 00:20:31,479
That'd be asking for a lot.

313
00:20:31,771 --> 00:20:33,815
It's okay. You just need to be more sure
of yourself.

314
00:20:36,025 --> 00:20:37,652
I'll wait for you.

315
00:20:38,236 --> 00:20:40,905
I'm really good at waiting
once I set my mind to it.

316
00:20:46,119 --> 00:20:48,413
Could you give me your hand?

317
00:20:55,795 --> 00:20:57,422
But don't hesitate to run to me

318
00:20:59,132 --> 00:21:00,759
once your mind's made up.

319
00:21:15,565 --> 00:21:17,525
And five.

320
00:21:17,609 --> 00:21:19,736
Breathe out as you pull.

321
00:21:19,819 --> 00:21:21,237
Six.

322
00:21:22,363 --> 00:21:24,949
Keep going. Seven.

323
00:21:26,075 --> 00:21:28,369
Give me a sec. Just keep going.

324
00:21:30,413 --> 00:21:32,040
Good work, Hyun-min.

325
00:21:32,540 --> 00:21:34,417
This time, you're going to cycle.

326
00:21:34,501 --> 00:21:36,628
I was on the elliptical until dusk!

327
00:21:36,711 --> 00:21:37,796
Let me do something else.

328
00:21:37,879 --> 00:21:40,757
You need to push yourself all the way
to maximize the gains.

329
00:21:40,924 --> 00:21:42,008
Here. Come on.

330
00:21:44,219 --> 00:21:45,220
You can do it.

331
00:21:47,847 --> 00:21:49,015
You're doing great.

332
00:21:49,307 --> 00:21:53,561
You have to carry me on your back
if I can't walk home, okay?

333
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:54,854
Absolutely.

334
00:21:55,063 --> 00:21:57,524
Come on. Put your feet on the pedals.

335
00:21:58,399 --> 00:21:59,567
And push hard!

336
00:22:01,194 --> 00:22:02,403
Keep going!

337
00:22:10,370 --> 00:22:12,664
- Good work.
- Good work.

338
00:22:18,378 --> 00:22:20,672
- Bye.
- Great work today.

339
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:26,636
Let's do five more in this position.

340
00:22:26,719 --> 00:22:28,304
Go slowly.

341
00:22:28,972 --> 00:22:29,973
Huh?

342
00:22:30,890 --> 00:22:33,518
Two, three

343
00:22:34,227 --> 00:22:36,855
four, five...

344
00:22:38,314 --> 00:22:40,817
Pull all the way.

345
00:22:41,442 --> 00:22:43,695
Right on. And 20!

346
00:22:43,778 --> 00:22:45,780
Alright, onto the next side.

347
00:22:46,531 --> 00:22:48,199
Keep your abs tucked.

348
00:22:49,033 --> 00:22:51,202
Breathe out as you pull with your muscles.

349
00:22:52,912 --> 00:22:54,038
Three...

350
00:22:56,916 --> 00:22:57,959
Four...

351
00:22:59,502 --> 00:23:01,296
- I love these shoes.
- The shoes!

352
00:23:01,754 --> 00:23:03,506
They fit perfectly. Where are you headed?

353
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:04,591
This way!

354
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,143
- Really?
- Yeah.

355
00:23:15,226 --> 00:23:17,061
No wonder you're so buff!

356
00:23:17,145 --> 00:23:18,229
You're too nice.

357
00:23:18,771 --> 00:23:21,065
- Do you have a personal trainer?
- No, I don't.

358
00:23:21,149 --> 00:23:23,359
- I see.
- I'm heading this way.

359
00:23:23,693 --> 00:23:24,694
Okay.

360
00:23:24,986 --> 00:23:26,738
- See you around.
- Bye!

361
00:23:32,243 --> 00:23:33,912
Where is she going?

362
00:23:56,726 --> 00:23:57,727
Soonmu Market?

363
00:23:58,311 --> 00:23:59,354
- Hello.
- Hi.

364
00:24:06,611 --> 00:24:09,072
What? Another one?

365
00:24:12,992 --> 00:24:14,661
What are they saying?

366
00:24:24,754 --> 00:24:26,089
Oh, gosh.

367
00:24:27,048 --> 00:24:28,216
What the heck?

368
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:34,347
Hmm? Seung-jun?

369
00:24:34,430 --> 00:24:36,391
Have you been following me? Why?

370
00:24:37,934 --> 00:24:38,977
Well...

371
00:24:40,228 --> 00:24:42,313
I... Well...

372
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,235
One of the guys at the gym told me

373
00:24:47,485 --> 00:24:49,737
he saw you on a dating app.

374
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:52,740
Someone at your gym?

375
00:24:55,076 --> 00:24:56,119
So?

376
00:24:57,745 --> 00:25:00,498
I just saw you leaving the gym with him.

377
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,669
I didn't meet him on a dating app.

378
00:25:04,752 --> 00:25:06,629
He definitely said it was an app.

379
00:25:08,798 --> 00:25:11,009
An app... Huh?

380
00:25:12,051 --> 00:25:13,511
It's Soonmu Market.

381
00:25:13,594 --> 00:25:15,596
He bought sneakers from me.

382
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:17,098
He has small feet.

383
00:25:17,473 --> 00:25:21,644
I sell things I don't use
and buy things I need.

384
00:25:22,186 --> 00:25:24,731
So, the guy just now...

385
00:25:27,483 --> 00:25:28,526
Here!

386
00:25:29,402 --> 00:25:32,071
I got the book you tore.

387
00:25:32,155 --> 00:25:34,574
I wanted the whole set.

388
00:25:36,159 --> 00:25:37,660
My gosh!

389
00:25:39,203 --> 00:25:42,081
I was so scared,
thinking it was something else!

390
00:25:42,165 --> 00:25:44,375
- Hmm?
- I thought you were someone

391
00:25:44,625 --> 00:25:46,169
who used dating apps

392
00:25:46,252 --> 00:25:49,922
and just slept around with random guys.
I was so scared.

393
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:52,884
I wasn't even sure
if I should keep texting you.

394
00:25:56,095 --> 00:25:59,891
I want a serious relationship.

395
00:26:02,143 --> 00:26:03,186
Oh...

396
00:26:09,150 --> 00:26:11,360
But yeah, I've used dating apps.

397
00:26:14,530 --> 00:26:15,531
Huh?

398
00:26:18,576 --> 00:26:20,745
Dating apps. I've used them.

399
00:26:22,455 --> 00:26:24,415
Does that change your impression of me?

400
00:26:35,885 --> 00:26:39,722
My stomach doesn't hurt anymore,
but I can't sleep.

401
00:26:55,530 --> 00:26:57,657
Dating apps. I've used them.

402
00:26:57,907 --> 00:26:59,575
Does that change your impression of me?

403
00:27:01,369 --> 00:27:03,788
My stomach hurts when I have cold food.

404
00:27:04,956 --> 00:27:06,457
But now that my heart feels cold

405
00:27:09,252 --> 00:27:10,795
my nose is tingling.

406
00:27:28,938 --> 00:27:30,314
Notebook and pen? Okay.

407
00:27:30,398 --> 00:27:32,316
I can make mistakes.

408
00:27:32,567 --> 00:27:35,069
But I will learn from them. Alright.

409
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:37,905
But the most important thing is

410
00:27:38,281 --> 00:27:39,866
to ask questions when I'm confused.

411
00:27:39,949 --> 00:27:41,492
- Acting like I know it is...
- Hey.

412
00:27:43,244 --> 00:27:44,537
Good morning.

413
00:27:44,704 --> 00:27:46,664
Was that your affirmation
for the first day?

414
00:27:47,206 --> 00:27:48,207
Yeah.

415
00:27:48,749 --> 00:27:49,917
Add one more thing to it.

416
00:27:50,001 --> 00:27:52,461
Don't panic,
even if things don't go as expected.

417
00:27:53,504 --> 00:27:54,505
Okay.

418
00:27:54,589 --> 00:27:56,299
- Let's head in.
- Okay!

419
00:28:02,054 --> 00:28:05,391
Sae-byeok? Is she our new hire?

420
00:28:05,766 --> 00:28:07,185
What about the hotel?

421
00:28:07,602 --> 00:28:10,813
My internship at the hotel has ended.

422
00:28:13,983 --> 00:28:16,360
Did you hurt your arm?

423
00:28:16,819 --> 00:28:18,362
Oh, this?

424
00:28:18,821 --> 00:28:21,699
I panicked and slipped

425
00:28:21,782 --> 00:28:23,034
on a rainy and slippery day.

426
00:28:23,492 --> 00:28:25,203
Always be careful, through and through.

427
00:28:25,286 --> 00:28:26,329
Got it.

428
00:28:26,454 --> 00:28:28,206
What year were you born in?

429
00:28:28,414 --> 00:28:29,999
In 1999? Or 1998?

430
00:28:30,082 --> 00:28:31,250
I was born in 2000.

431
00:28:32,585 --> 00:28:35,296
- She's the youngest!
- It's your lucky day!

432
00:28:35,630 --> 00:28:37,715
- Ms. Sim.
- Oh, yes.

433
00:28:37,798 --> 00:28:40,635
- Can you come to sign your contract?
- Oh, sure.

434
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:41,761
- Oh, no.
- Oh, gosh.

435
00:28:42,470 --> 00:28:43,596
I told you to be careful.

436
00:28:47,558 --> 00:28:48,893
Don't panic.

437
00:28:48,976 --> 00:28:50,144
Or be so surprised.

438
00:28:54,482 --> 00:28:56,192
You can come in and leave anytime

439
00:28:56,359 --> 00:28:59,737
but try to work and rest
when everyone's doing the same.

440
00:29:00,529 --> 00:29:02,615
It's a rough environment to work in

441
00:29:02,698 --> 00:29:05,493
so save your best clothes for the weekend.

442
00:29:05,576 --> 00:29:06,577
Yes, sir.

443
00:29:07,286 --> 00:29:09,372
You look great in hoodies.

444
00:29:09,455 --> 00:29:11,415
- Don't you hear that a lot?
- Thank you.

445
00:29:11,499 --> 00:29:13,125
- I've never been told that.
- I see.

446
00:29:13,209 --> 00:29:14,919
Alright! This is the woodworking room.

447
00:29:15,628 --> 00:29:18,047
You can get your training from Tae-seop
as you assist him.

448
00:29:18,130 --> 00:29:19,507
Let's have a welcome party soon.

449
00:29:19,590 --> 00:29:20,758
Bo-yoon! Jin-su!

450
00:29:20,841 --> 00:29:21,926
- Coming!
- Coming!

451
00:29:26,514 --> 00:29:27,682
Have a seat.

452
00:29:30,017 --> 00:29:31,602
- 1,300cm.
- Okay, 1,300cm.

453
00:29:32,478 --> 00:29:33,479
And 450cm.

454
00:29:33,562 --> 00:29:34,689
What are you guys doing?

455
00:29:34,772 --> 00:29:36,607
We're making a custom-made chair for you.

456
00:29:36,691 --> 00:29:37,817
It's a ritual at HOME.

457
00:29:37,900 --> 00:29:41,028
We're a woodworking studio.
We can't just sit on any chair.

458
00:29:41,696 --> 00:29:43,322
- Sae-byeok.
- Yes!

459
00:29:48,786 --> 00:29:50,079
You remember this tray table?

460
00:29:50,162 --> 00:29:51,706
Of course!

461
00:29:51,956 --> 00:29:53,791
You already finished it?

462
00:29:53,874 --> 00:29:57,378
Yeah, we'll check them today
and ship them to the hotel tomorrow.

463
00:29:57,962 --> 00:29:59,880
- Help us.
- Okay.

464
00:30:00,548 --> 00:30:01,757
This is your first task.

465
00:30:02,425 --> 00:30:03,509
Yeah, my first task!

466
00:30:06,929 --> 00:30:09,974
Where are you going after checking out?
Dr. Shin's?

467
00:30:10,099 --> 00:30:12,643
No, I'll go to Hannam-dong first.

468
00:30:13,686 --> 00:30:15,313
I just want to get some good rest.

469
00:30:15,396 --> 00:30:19,859
You know the agency's been through a lot
with the scandal, right?

470
00:30:20,776 --> 00:30:22,611
Yeah, I was just reading the scripts.

471
00:30:22,778 --> 00:30:24,280
Why did you send me so many?

472
00:30:24,363 --> 00:30:26,324
There were way more.
I picked a few good ones.

473
00:30:26,657 --> 00:30:30,369
You definitely proved yourself
as Korea's biggest queen of romance now.

474
00:30:31,370 --> 00:30:34,081
I think it's Ui-yeong.
Let me call you once I head home.

475
00:30:35,666 --> 00:30:36,667
Come in.

476
00:30:41,130 --> 00:30:43,507
You can just pack the necessities
and check out.

477
00:30:43,591 --> 00:30:45,968
The hotel van will deliver the rest
to your home.

478
00:30:47,219 --> 00:30:48,220
Thanks.

479
00:30:54,226 --> 00:30:55,227
It's Seasons of Us.

480
00:30:55,311 --> 00:30:56,520
SEASONS OF US

481
00:30:58,898 --> 00:31:00,816
Oh, that?

482
00:31:02,735 --> 00:31:03,944
You want it?

483
00:31:04,779 --> 00:31:06,697
Really? Are you sure I can have it?

484
00:31:07,156 --> 00:31:09,658
Yeah, you're my fan. Hold on.

485
00:31:14,205 --> 00:31:16,207
Thanks for all your help. I appreciate it.

486
00:31:16,540 --> 00:31:17,541
It was nothing.

487
00:31:22,588 --> 00:31:26,592
I HOPE YOUR BRIEF LIFE IS FILLED
WITH MANY DAYS OF LOVE

488
00:31:35,768 --> 00:31:37,520
Ui-yeong, what are you doing on Saturday?

489
00:31:37,603 --> 00:31:38,813
Let's get lunch or dinner.

490
00:31:46,904 --> 00:31:47,988
You can check your phone.

491
00:31:48,072 --> 00:31:49,407
Oh, okay.

492
00:31:50,574 --> 00:31:51,909
You still owe me.

493
00:31:52,159 --> 00:31:55,121
I may like you,
but that doesn't mean you're off the hook.

494
00:31:57,331 --> 00:31:59,500
Are you seeing someone?

495
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,836
No, I'm not.

496
00:32:02,294 --> 00:32:05,089
Get on it, then.
Don't waste the good weather.

497
00:32:07,341 --> 00:32:08,426
The issue is

498
00:32:09,260 --> 00:32:11,470
I don't understand my own feelings.

499
00:32:12,388 --> 00:32:15,433
You must've been popular your whole life.

500
00:32:16,892 --> 00:32:18,269
Well, I can't deny that.

501
00:32:19,019 --> 00:32:20,896
You know how people say

502
00:32:21,814 --> 00:32:24,984
they feel sure about wanting to spend
the rest of their lives with someone?

503
00:32:25,067 --> 00:32:27,069
I don't know if I feel that way.

504
00:32:27,528 --> 00:32:28,529
There were...

505
00:32:29,488 --> 00:32:31,115
some moments when I just felt sure.

506
00:32:32,324 --> 00:32:36,829
Once you collect the many moments
of falling for someone

507
00:32:37,204 --> 00:32:40,040
you reach a certain threshold

508
00:32:40,791 --> 00:32:44,879
and at that point,
you just get so sad and hurt without them.

509
00:32:46,505 --> 00:32:47,798
That's when you realize

510
00:32:50,050 --> 00:32:51,177
that they're the one.

511
00:32:52,553 --> 00:32:53,637
Threshold...

512
00:32:54,847 --> 00:32:57,057
- Like an allergic reaction?
- Exactly.

513
00:32:57,475 --> 00:33:00,019
Isn't falling in love another form
of immune system failure?

514
00:33:02,521 --> 00:33:04,690
So, just spend more time with them.

515
00:33:04,773 --> 00:33:07,443
Look into their eyes
and talk to them more.

516
00:33:07,526 --> 00:33:10,946
Don't just think about it alone.
You'll have moments where you become sure

517
00:33:11,071 --> 00:33:12,698
when you spend more time together.

518
00:33:24,668 --> 00:33:25,669
Thank you.

519
00:33:28,005 --> 00:33:29,423
Thank you. It was really good.

520
00:33:30,341 --> 00:33:32,259
Thanks for the great stay.

521
00:33:32,593 --> 00:33:34,220
- See you again.
- See you.

522
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:46,190
Sure, see you on Saturday.

523
00:33:46,482 --> 00:33:47,691
You can choose what to eat.

524
00:33:47,775 --> 00:33:48,817
Yes!

525
00:33:51,070 --> 00:33:52,363
Did something good happen?

526
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:54,365
What's this for?

527
00:34:02,998 --> 00:34:04,542
Push them in all the way.

528
00:34:05,042 --> 00:34:06,168
We got this.

529
00:34:06,252 --> 00:34:07,711
Leave it to us. That's helping.

530
00:34:07,795 --> 00:34:08,963
- Wait.
- Hey.

531
00:34:09,046 --> 00:34:11,340
- Here, wear these gloves.
- Okay.

532
00:34:12,550 --> 00:34:13,551
Hey.

533
00:34:15,469 --> 00:34:16,595
You sure you're not going?

534
00:34:17,137 --> 00:34:20,099
This is a perfect chance to run into her!

535
00:34:20,182 --> 00:34:21,850
Just go with Sae-byeok.

536
00:34:22,226 --> 00:34:23,602
I did everything I could.

537
00:34:23,894 --> 00:34:26,272
What do you mean? Do more!

538
00:34:26,355 --> 00:34:28,065
What's got your spirit down like that?

539
00:34:28,357 --> 00:34:29,775
- Sae-byeok.
- Yes?

540
00:34:31,402 --> 00:34:32,987
Your first trip out. Good luck.

541
00:34:33,070 --> 00:34:34,738
- Everyone will be so surprised.
- Yeah.

542
00:34:36,532 --> 00:34:37,866
Let's go.

543
00:34:37,950 --> 00:34:39,034
Let's go now!

544
00:34:58,220 --> 00:35:00,556
- Hello.
- Hello!

545
00:35:00,889 --> 00:35:01,890
This way.

546
00:35:02,641 --> 00:35:05,352
I thought Mr. Song would come, not you.

547
00:35:05,436 --> 00:35:08,314
Oh, work's been busy.

548
00:35:08,856 --> 00:35:10,691
But... Ta-da!

549
00:35:12,276 --> 00:35:13,777
- Huh? Sae-byeok!
- Huh?

550
00:35:13,944 --> 00:35:16,071
Why are you coming out of that truck?

551
00:35:16,155 --> 00:35:18,073
I got hired at HOME.

552
00:35:18,157 --> 00:35:20,618
What? That's amazing!

553
00:35:20,826 --> 00:35:22,578
What a big surprise!

554
00:35:22,661 --> 00:35:25,539
I didn't expect this job offer, either.

555
00:35:25,623 --> 00:35:28,459
I was only fixated on what I was bad at

556
00:35:28,542 --> 00:35:31,128
but Mr. Song saw good things in me.

557
00:35:32,004 --> 00:35:33,672
Isn't he so thoughtful?

558
00:35:34,089 --> 00:35:37,384
Why didn't you tell us sooner?
It's good news!

559
00:35:37,593 --> 00:35:39,595
What a cheeky girl! Congrats!

560
00:35:39,678 --> 00:35:42,014
I wasn't trying to keep it a secret.

561
00:35:42,097 --> 00:35:44,183
I wanted to tell you at the farewell party

562
00:35:44,266 --> 00:35:45,601
but we kept rescheduling.

563
00:35:45,684 --> 00:35:47,311
You haven't had a farewell yet?

564
00:35:47,394 --> 00:35:49,229
No, not yet.

565
00:35:50,314 --> 00:35:51,690
Should we move the boxes first?

566
00:35:51,774 --> 00:35:53,108
Yeah, this way.

567
00:35:53,192 --> 00:35:55,027
Isn't this such great news?

568
00:35:55,110 --> 00:35:56,236
I'm so happy for her!

569
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:58,364
- I can't believe she didn't tell us!
- Take one.

570
00:35:58,447 --> 00:35:59,698
WHISKEY BOXES IN THE GUEST SUITES
AT THE HILL SEOUL'S POP-UP

571
00:35:59,782 --> 00:36:00,783
- Bye!
- Bye!

572
00:36:00,866 --> 00:36:01,992
- Bye!
- See you!

573
00:36:02,076 --> 00:36:03,118
Bye, Sae-byeok!

574
00:36:07,748 --> 00:36:09,124
- Let's go.
- Yes, sir.

575
00:36:10,250 --> 00:36:11,460
- Sae-byeok.
- Yeah?

576
00:36:11,543 --> 00:36:12,961
About your farewell party.

577
00:36:13,045 --> 00:36:15,255
There's nothing to be sad about anymore.

578
00:36:16,048 --> 00:36:17,800
- No.
- Why don't we have a big party

579
00:36:17,883 --> 00:36:19,635
for the farewell and the welcome?

580
00:36:19,968 --> 00:36:21,553
It could be a job transfer party.

581
00:36:23,639 --> 00:36:25,933
- No?
- That sounds good.

582
00:36:26,016 --> 00:36:28,227
OFFER FOR PARTICIPATION
IN THE FINDING DAILY HARMONY EXHIBITION

583
00:36:28,310 --> 00:36:29,436
HELLO, THIS IS THE EXHIBITION TEAM
AT GALLERY RYE

584
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:32,690
WE'D LIKE TO HAVE MR. SONG TAE-SEOP
PARTICIPATE IN THE EXHIBITION

585
00:36:34,525 --> 00:36:35,901
SEND AN EVENING MESSAGE

586
00:36:42,241 --> 00:36:46,286
ALARMS

587
00:36:51,291 --> 00:36:53,043
I'll do it all.

588
00:36:53,961 --> 00:36:55,921
Are you busy, Mr. Song?

589
00:36:56,004 --> 00:36:57,297
Why? Do you need help?

590
00:36:57,381 --> 00:36:59,466
Yeah, I need someone to help
with the sanding.

591
00:36:59,675 --> 00:37:02,636
Okay, I'll be right over.
I just need to write an e-mail.

592
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:04,096
Okay, thank you.

593
00:37:18,694 --> 00:37:19,987
He's been so quiet.

594
00:37:31,498 --> 00:37:32,541
Hello?

595
00:37:33,041 --> 00:37:35,043
Is this Mr. Shin Ji-su?

596
00:37:35,252 --> 00:37:37,004
I'm calling about the acting audition.

597
00:37:37,463 --> 00:37:39,798
Yes, that's me.

598
00:37:42,468 --> 00:37:43,552
Oh, yes.

599
00:37:44,928 --> 00:37:46,013
I can do that.

600
00:38:01,904 --> 00:38:03,822
Once you collect the many moments

601
00:38:03,906 --> 00:38:06,533
of falling for someone

602
00:38:06,784 --> 00:38:09,661
you reach a certain threshold

603
00:38:10,370 --> 00:38:14,374
and at that point,
you just get so sad and hurt without them.

604
00:38:35,979 --> 00:38:38,273
HEARTBURN AND INDIGESTION MEDICINE

605
00:38:52,830 --> 00:38:54,790
- Ui-yeong, about the farewell party.
- Yeah?

606
00:38:54,873 --> 00:38:59,169
Sae-byeok wants it this Saturday
at Songi Spicy Chicken Feet.

607
00:38:59,253 --> 00:39:02,047
Chef Park and Mr. Eun are free that day.

608
00:39:03,507 --> 00:39:04,508
This Saturday?

609
00:39:05,217 --> 00:39:06,844
I do have plans.

610
00:39:06,927 --> 00:39:08,887
Okay, we'll do it another day, then.

611
00:39:09,429 --> 00:39:12,641
No, it's hard to find a day
that works for everyone.

612
00:39:12,891 --> 00:39:15,102
I'll just join you guys a bit late.

613
00:39:15,185 --> 00:39:17,104
- Okay, Saturday it is, then.
- Okay.

614
00:39:17,980 --> 00:39:20,315
How come you're not going on a date?
It's Saturday.

615
00:39:21,984 --> 00:39:24,027
Yeah, that's over.

616
00:39:25,070 --> 00:39:27,406
I need a drink. I need this party.

617
00:39:29,199 --> 00:39:30,617
I'm going to drink tons.

618
00:39:32,953 --> 00:39:35,330
How can I just choose one?

619
00:39:35,455 --> 00:39:36,790
One is my teacher for life

620
00:39:36,874 --> 00:39:39,167
and the other is my role model.

621
00:39:39,251 --> 00:39:40,961
I can't choose one. No way.

622
00:39:41,044 --> 00:39:42,421
Please, you two go ahead.

623
00:39:42,921 --> 00:39:44,423
- Good work.
- Thank you.

624
00:39:44,506 --> 00:39:45,841
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

625
00:39:46,592 --> 00:39:47,843
Come here.

626
00:39:48,343 --> 00:39:50,220
How did it go? Tell me.

627
00:39:54,641 --> 00:39:55,642
Mr. Shin.

628
00:39:55,851 --> 00:39:57,728
- This way, please.
- Okay.

629
00:40:02,691 --> 00:40:04,401
- Hello.
- Hello.

630
00:40:04,484 --> 00:40:05,903
- Hello.
- Hello.

631
00:40:07,112 --> 00:40:08,989
- He's Mr. Shin Ji-su.
- Okay.

632
00:40:12,117 --> 00:40:13,493
Mr. Shin Ji-su?

633
00:40:13,577 --> 00:40:14,870
Yes, I'm Shin Ji-su.

634
00:40:14,953 --> 00:40:18,123
The directing team went
to see your play together

635
00:40:18,665 --> 00:40:21,001
and left our business card
because they liked your vibe.

636
00:40:21,168 --> 00:40:23,587
I thought you weren't interested
because you didn't call.

637
00:40:25,547 --> 00:40:27,299
I'm glad to hear you enjoyed my acting.

638
00:40:27,674 --> 00:40:30,218
I recently left the troupe
due to personal reasons.

639
00:40:31,094 --> 00:40:32,888
I'm working hard to do whatever I can.

640
00:40:34,389 --> 00:40:35,807
Do you like to exercise?

641
00:40:36,475 --> 00:40:39,728
Yeah, I lift weights to stay in shape.

642
00:40:39,811 --> 00:40:40,979
- You lift?
- Yes.

643
00:40:41,229 --> 00:40:43,190
Shin Ji-su? That's the guy.

644
00:40:43,523 --> 00:40:45,651
Son Jeong-a's stepson.
He was the talk of the town.

645
00:40:45,734 --> 00:40:47,194
Oh! Yeah, I think that's him.

646
00:40:49,196 --> 00:40:50,864
Okay, then.

647
00:40:51,949 --> 00:40:52,950
This car.

648
00:40:54,952 --> 00:40:58,330
It's a 2017 model,
and it's been driven about 40,000km.

649
00:40:58,413 --> 00:40:59,665
No accidents, of course.

650
00:41:00,374 --> 00:41:01,833
It's in perfect condition outside.

651
00:41:02,459 --> 00:41:05,087
This is perfect for your budget.

652
00:41:05,545 --> 00:41:07,214
You can go inside. Here, this way.

653
00:41:07,965 --> 00:41:08,966
Okay.

654
00:41:10,008 --> 00:41:12,386
A non-smoking lady drove it,
so there's no stench.

655
00:41:13,971 --> 00:41:15,013
Take your time.

656
00:42:04,855 --> 00:42:06,690
SEASONS OF US

657
00:42:08,608 --> 00:42:10,068
Don't just think about it alone.

658
00:42:10,152 --> 00:42:11,903
You'll have moments where you become sure

659
00:42:12,404 --> 00:42:14,114
when you spend more time together.

660
00:42:18,243 --> 00:42:20,537
Ui-yeong, come out when you're ready.

661
00:42:21,371 --> 00:42:22,372
"Come out"?

662
00:42:26,668 --> 00:42:27,669
Ui-yeong!

663
00:42:28,628 --> 00:42:29,629
Hey.

664
00:42:32,007 --> 00:42:33,633
We could've met at the restaurant.

665
00:42:38,889 --> 00:42:39,973
What's with the car?

666
00:42:40,432 --> 00:42:42,225
- It's mine.
- Huh?

667
00:42:42,476 --> 00:42:45,145
I needed one to keep my things
while driving to sets.

668
00:42:45,979 --> 00:42:47,314
What about your motorcycle?

669
00:42:47,731 --> 00:42:49,566
Just hop in. Let's go somewhere nice.

670
00:42:50,233 --> 00:42:51,234
Watch your head.

671
00:43:04,664 --> 00:43:05,957
You're my first passenger.

672
00:43:06,875 --> 00:43:07,918
Be honored.

673
00:43:08,376 --> 00:43:09,920
Sure, what an honor.

674
00:43:12,047 --> 00:43:14,716
Are we going to a restaurant far away?

675
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:16,760
- Why?
- I need to go

676
00:43:16,843 --> 00:43:19,221
to my intern's farewell party for dinner.

677
00:43:19,930 --> 00:43:23,391
I told them I'd join them later,
thinking we were eating near here.

678
00:43:24,059 --> 00:43:25,268
It's still early in the day.

679
00:43:25,352 --> 00:43:27,562
We can have lunch, get some coffee

680
00:43:27,646 --> 00:43:29,189
and still be back by 7 or 8 p.m.

681
00:43:29,314 --> 00:43:31,441
Oh, that's good enough.

682
00:43:31,525 --> 00:43:32,567
Yeah.

683
00:43:36,279 --> 00:43:41,368
Maybe I'm too used to seeing you
looking for coffee like a zombie.

684
00:43:42,744 --> 00:43:43,870
You look pretty today.

685
00:43:45,872 --> 00:43:46,873
That's random.

686
00:43:48,875 --> 00:43:51,753
Of course, I look better today
than when I go to work.

687
00:43:52,129 --> 00:43:53,713
I should've dressed better, too.

688
00:43:54,131 --> 00:43:56,633
I didn't want to dress up
and get so awkward, though.

689
00:44:15,902 --> 00:44:18,238
- Yeah.
- Hey, Tae-seop.

690
00:44:18,405 --> 00:44:21,032
What time did you leave work?
Did you work until late?

691
00:44:21,116 --> 00:44:22,993
Yeah, I had to help the guys
with some stuff

692
00:44:23,076 --> 00:44:25,537
and brainstorm some ideas
for the exhibition.

693
00:44:25,620 --> 00:44:29,666
You think we can submit to the magazine
the entries we've presented at fairs?

694
00:44:29,749 --> 00:44:31,126
It'll be good to have new works.

695
00:44:31,209 --> 00:44:32,502
Maybe add one new thing.

696
00:44:34,254 --> 00:44:36,464
By the way, did you choose
where we're meeting today?

697
00:44:36,548 --> 00:44:37,799
No, Sae-byeok did.

698
00:44:37,883 --> 00:44:40,552
Dress nice, okay?

699
00:44:41,094 --> 00:44:43,638
Seeing her bosses well-dressed
will make her feel prouder.

700
00:44:43,722 --> 00:44:46,766
Ridiculous. Do I really have to go?

701
00:44:46,850 --> 00:44:50,187
Of course! How can a CEO not come
to the welcome party?

702
00:44:50,270 --> 00:44:52,189
Even I'm taking Sua!

703
00:44:52,898 --> 00:44:55,233
- Fine, see you.
- Bye.

704
00:45:05,702 --> 00:45:06,786
Try this, too.

705
00:45:08,622 --> 00:45:10,540
Stop feeding me.
You should have some, too.

706
00:45:10,624 --> 00:45:12,751
Seeing you eat well makes me full.

707
00:45:12,834 --> 00:45:14,002
That's a lie.

708
00:45:14,127 --> 00:45:15,962
You're going to have ramyeon
at home later.

709
00:45:16,296 --> 00:45:17,964
Wait, that's a great idea.

710
00:45:18,298 --> 00:45:20,926
Ramyeon is the best dessert
after a meaty meal.

711
00:45:21,718 --> 00:45:23,678
That's true. I prefer jjajang ramyeon.

712
00:45:23,762 --> 00:45:25,680
With a sunny-side-up on top.

713
00:45:25,764 --> 00:45:26,890
Okay, sunny-side-up.

714
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:30,101
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

715
00:45:31,228 --> 00:45:33,271
This table is wobbly.

716
00:45:33,688 --> 00:45:35,815
Sorry, I'll take you to a new table.

717
00:45:35,899 --> 00:45:36,942
- Okay.
- Thank you.

718
00:45:43,365 --> 00:45:44,407
- All good.
- All good.

719
00:45:51,581 --> 00:45:52,582
Something wrong?

720
00:45:53,124 --> 00:45:56,044
Huh? Oh, nothing.
Let's get back to eating.

721
00:45:59,881 --> 00:46:01,258
I haven't been here in forever.

722
00:46:01,341 --> 00:46:03,510
SONGI SPICY CHICKEN FEET

723
00:46:03,593 --> 00:46:04,928
Oh, hello!

724
00:46:05,011 --> 00:46:06,388
You could've just waited inside!

725
00:46:07,931 --> 00:46:09,140
Hi, Sua.

726
00:46:09,599 --> 00:46:10,892
Congrats on getting hired.

727
00:46:11,226 --> 00:46:13,061
I look forward to seeing you grow.

728
00:46:13,144 --> 00:46:14,145
Oh, thanks.

729
00:46:15,772 --> 00:46:18,817
Sua, I'm worried about your growth.

730
00:46:18,900 --> 00:46:21,403
How did you end up choosing this place?

731
00:46:21,486 --> 00:46:22,779
Oh, my supervisors...

732
00:46:23,655 --> 00:46:26,658
I mean, my ex-supervisors at the hotel
love this place.

733
00:46:26,741 --> 00:46:29,661
- What?
- Can you not eat chicken feet?

734
00:46:29,744 --> 00:46:30,829
Oh, that's not it.

735
00:46:30,912 --> 00:46:32,163
I suggested a joint party.

736
00:46:32,914 --> 00:46:35,292
The hotel staff wanted to hold
a farewell party for her.

737
00:46:35,375 --> 00:46:37,794
We know them, anyway.
It'll be nice to see everyone.

738
00:46:37,877 --> 00:46:39,587
I never asked you to do this.

739
00:46:39,671 --> 00:46:41,089
Ui-yeong's coming, too, right?

740
00:46:41,172 --> 00:46:43,383
Yeah, she'll just be a bit late.
She's busy today.

741
00:46:43,842 --> 00:46:45,093
Is that so?

742
00:46:45,635 --> 00:46:49,264
She'll be a bit late, but she's coming!
Let's head in.

743
00:46:49,931 --> 00:46:52,183
I'll call Ui-yeong first and head in.

744
00:46:52,267 --> 00:46:53,268
Okay.

745
00:46:53,351 --> 00:46:55,812
- Grandma!
- Sua!

746
00:46:55,895 --> 00:46:58,523
There's my Sua!

747
00:46:58,606 --> 00:47:02,152
My sweet girl!
You look more and more like your dad.

748
00:47:02,986 --> 00:47:04,821
We have a big party coming today.

749
00:47:05,196 --> 00:47:06,531
We're having a staff party

750
00:47:06,614 --> 00:47:08,783
because we just hired
the intern from the hotel.

751
00:47:08,867 --> 00:47:10,827
- I see.
- Could you watch Sua?

752
00:47:10,910 --> 00:47:12,620
Don't worry, I got her.

753
00:47:13,163 --> 00:47:15,457
Let's have a blast!

754
00:47:16,041 --> 00:47:17,042
Yes!

755
00:47:17,125 --> 00:47:19,961
Does that mean that lady is coming, too?

756
00:47:20,545 --> 00:47:21,880
Oh, yeah.

757
00:47:25,091 --> 00:47:27,677
- My gosh!
- Hello!

758
00:47:28,136 --> 00:47:30,055
- Finally!
- What's going on?

759
00:47:30,138 --> 00:47:31,806
Please use words!

760
00:47:31,890 --> 00:47:33,725
- Did you dine and dash?
- No.

761
00:47:33,808 --> 00:47:34,809
I'll pay for him.

762
00:47:34,893 --> 00:47:36,478
Yeah, he's never paid us.

763
00:47:41,816 --> 00:47:44,694
It's a big party today!

764
00:47:46,529 --> 00:47:48,573
- You're the best!
- Be careful.

765
00:47:48,656 --> 00:47:49,908
Here you go. Be careful.

766
00:47:49,991 --> 00:47:52,535
You're his mother?
I thought you were his sister!

767
00:47:53,745 --> 00:47:56,623
It's on us today! Eat up!

768
00:47:57,749 --> 00:47:59,626
What? I brought the hotel's company card.

769
00:47:59,709 --> 00:48:03,213
No, I'll only charge you
for the drinks on the table now.

770
00:48:03,296 --> 00:48:05,423
Grab any drink from the fridge for free!

771
00:48:05,507 --> 00:48:07,467
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

772
00:48:07,550 --> 00:48:08,927
Thank you so much, miss!

773
00:48:09,594 --> 00:48:11,721
You have to pace yourself, okay?

774
00:48:11,805 --> 00:48:14,432
Ui-yeong isn't here yet,
so just drink water for now.

775
00:48:15,225 --> 00:48:16,559
- Oh, thanks.
- Pace yourself.

776
00:48:16,643 --> 00:48:17,852
This is really good.

777
00:48:17,936 --> 00:48:19,938
Mr. Eun, say something.

778
00:48:20,021 --> 00:48:21,022
Huh?

779
00:48:24,192 --> 00:48:25,235
Oh, gosh.

780
00:48:26,361 --> 00:48:29,322
The sun might still be up as it's summer

781
00:48:29,406 --> 00:48:32,117
but our night has begun!

782
00:48:33,201 --> 00:48:36,621
It's my 40th year of working

783
00:48:37,330 --> 00:48:40,500
and this is the smoothest job transfer
I've seen.

784
00:48:40,583 --> 00:48:42,836
We can send her off with a big smile

785
00:48:42,919 --> 00:48:45,505
because we know how sincere she was
about the work she did.

786
00:48:46,131 --> 00:48:47,173
Goodbye.

787
00:48:47,632 --> 00:48:49,217
Please be kind to our Sae-byeok.

788
00:48:49,342 --> 00:48:50,510
- Okay.
- Yes, sir!

789
00:48:50,593 --> 00:48:53,680
Sae-byeok, you'd better live
the best life of all!

790
00:48:53,763 --> 00:48:56,141
- Goodbye!
- Welcome, Sae-byeok!

791
00:48:56,224 --> 00:48:58,351
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

792
00:49:00,562 --> 00:49:02,772
- Drink up!
- Right on!

793
00:49:04,274 --> 00:49:05,275
Here we go!

794
00:49:06,067 --> 00:49:08,194
Ride the wave!

795
00:49:08,278 --> 00:49:09,446
Right on!

796
00:49:10,572 --> 00:49:12,323
I guess I'm not walking home tonight.

797
00:49:34,262 --> 00:49:35,263
Here.

798
00:49:35,680 --> 00:49:37,724
Oh, thanks.

799
00:49:45,106 --> 00:49:48,026
Oh, how did that audition go?

800
00:49:50,069 --> 00:49:51,863
Awkward. It was my first time, after all.

801
00:49:53,615 --> 00:49:56,701
They told me to remove my tattoos
if I was serious about acting.

802
00:49:57,327 --> 00:49:58,828
Covering them costs extra.

803
00:49:59,954 --> 00:50:00,955
Your tattoos, too?

804
00:50:03,041 --> 00:50:05,043
Are you sure you're okay with this?

805
00:50:06,794 --> 00:50:07,795
What do you mean?

806
00:50:07,879 --> 00:50:10,798
It feels like you're pushing yourself
too hard.

807
00:50:11,049 --> 00:50:13,134
With the tattoo removal and the auditions.

808
00:50:13,218 --> 00:50:14,844
And the car, too.

809
00:50:16,095 --> 00:50:18,014
There's no rush, is there?

810
00:50:20,433 --> 00:50:21,434
I'm fine.

811
00:50:21,935 --> 00:50:23,353
No need to worry about it.

812
00:50:23,978 --> 00:50:26,439
I may not do much,
but I do well when I put my mind to it.

813
00:50:27,815 --> 00:50:30,735
I'm sure the audition went well, too.

814
00:50:32,070 --> 00:50:35,156
You're right. I'm sure you did well.

815
00:50:44,916 --> 00:50:46,167
Sae-byeok.

816
00:50:47,418 --> 00:50:48,920
What's taking Ui-yeong so long?

817
00:50:50,088 --> 00:50:52,590
Is she not here yet?

818
00:50:52,674 --> 00:50:55,635
I asked you first.

819
00:50:55,718 --> 00:50:56,719
Mr. Eun!

820
00:50:57,637 --> 00:50:59,847
Let me call Eui-yeong

821
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:01,849
right now.

822
00:51:01,933 --> 00:51:03,810
Tell her to hurry
before the drinks get warm!

823
00:51:03,893 --> 00:51:05,895
- Alright! Cheers!
- The HOME style.

824
00:51:06,062 --> 00:51:07,772
The HOME style?

825
00:51:52,358 --> 00:51:53,401
What about today?

826
00:51:54,777 --> 00:51:55,903
How did I do today?

827
00:51:57,363 --> 00:51:58,448
Did I do well?

828
00:52:03,411 --> 00:52:04,412
Ui-yeong.

829
00:52:05,079 --> 00:52:06,164
Oh, yeah.

830
00:52:06,581 --> 00:52:07,582
Did I...

831
00:52:09,208 --> 00:52:10,335
do well today?

832
00:52:11,461 --> 00:52:12,503
If so

833
00:52:13,880 --> 00:52:14,881
give me a reward.

834
00:52:16,716 --> 00:52:17,759
No.

835
00:52:21,804 --> 00:52:22,930
I'll take it myself.

836
00:52:28,227 --> 00:52:29,270
Sorry.

837
00:52:39,405 --> 00:52:40,531
You were...

838
00:52:42,325 --> 00:52:43,701
perfect in every way.

839
00:52:44,494 --> 00:52:45,495
But...

840
00:52:48,039 --> 00:52:49,123
I keep

841
00:52:50,375 --> 00:52:52,043
thinking about someone else.

842
00:52:56,881 --> 00:52:57,924
Ji-su

843
00:53:00,218 --> 00:53:02,303
- I like Tae-seop.
- Did you...

844
00:53:04,347 --> 00:53:05,932
really feel nothing for me?

845
00:53:11,521 --> 00:53:13,106
But don't hesitate to run to me

846
00:53:13,690 --> 00:53:15,108
once your mind's made up.

847
00:53:17,360 --> 00:53:18,945
I don't want to make Tae-seop

848
00:53:20,029 --> 00:53:22,699
wait any longer.

849
00:54:10,163 --> 00:54:11,414
What's your ETA?

850
00:54:11,664 --> 00:54:13,624
I think Mr. Song's exhausted

851
00:54:13,708 --> 00:54:15,793
but he's still here
because he wants to see you.

852
00:54:16,711 --> 00:54:19,881
SONG TAE-SEOP

853
00:54:29,223 --> 00:54:31,476
I want to play basketball.

854
00:54:32,101 --> 00:54:33,144
Basketball...

855
00:54:33,519 --> 00:54:34,937
- Hyun-min.
- Yeah?

856
00:54:35,271 --> 00:54:37,356
You want to go
for a second round of drinks?

857
00:54:37,440 --> 00:54:39,400
- You down?
- Heck yeah!

858
00:54:39,484 --> 00:54:42,278
- Right on!
- I'll take Hyun-min home.

859
00:54:42,361 --> 00:54:43,654
You can go and keep partying.

860
00:54:44,197 --> 00:54:46,949
Gosh, you're still a kid inside.

861
00:54:47,950 --> 00:54:49,619
Chef, do you also need help going home?

862
00:54:49,702 --> 00:54:51,245
No, I called a cab.

863
00:54:52,079 --> 00:54:53,456
But Ui-yeong's still not here.

864
00:54:53,539 --> 00:54:54,582
Ui-yeong!

865
00:54:54,874 --> 00:54:56,167
- My gosh!
- Oh, man.

866
00:54:56,375 --> 00:54:57,376
You scared us.

867
00:54:58,294 --> 00:54:59,378
We screwed up!

868
00:55:00,463 --> 00:55:01,464
Why?

869
00:55:01,631 --> 00:55:02,840
- Jin-su
- Yeah?

870
00:55:02,924 --> 00:55:04,300
use this card at the afterparty.

871
00:55:07,720 --> 00:55:09,680
- Yes!
- Get ready to head out!

872
00:55:09,764 --> 00:55:11,140
- Okay!
- What?

873
00:55:17,313 --> 00:55:18,981
Ms. Lee!

874
00:55:20,066 --> 00:55:22,026
Tae-seop went home, right?

875
00:55:22,109 --> 00:55:23,152
No idea.

876
00:55:24,111 --> 00:55:26,489
Why didn't the lady come?

877
00:55:27,281 --> 00:55:31,035
Sua's asleep now. You can take her home.

878
00:55:34,038 --> 00:55:35,122
Okay, see you.

879
00:55:37,166 --> 00:55:38,793
Fried chicken sounds good.

880
00:55:38,876 --> 00:55:40,920
Yeah, that's better than beef sashimi.

881
00:55:41,003 --> 00:55:42,547
No, you just don't get it.

882
00:55:42,630 --> 00:55:44,006
- We need beef sashimi.
- Yeah.

883
00:55:44,090 --> 00:55:45,591
Fried chicken could be better.

884
00:55:45,675 --> 00:55:47,844
- You just don't know your food.
- Come on.

885
00:55:47,927 --> 00:55:48,970
Sae-byeok!

886
00:55:49,053 --> 00:55:50,054
- Hello.
- Hello.

887
00:55:51,222 --> 00:55:52,723
- Ui-yeong!
- Hey.

888
00:55:52,807 --> 00:55:55,268
I missed you. What took you so long?

889
00:55:55,351 --> 00:55:57,019
Sorry, I'm so late.

890
00:55:57,395 --> 00:55:58,729
Did you drink a lot?

891
00:55:59,272 --> 00:56:00,314
Yeah, we did.

892
00:56:00,398 --> 00:56:01,983
We're having an afterparty. Join us.

893
00:56:02,149 --> 00:56:03,651
Oh, well...

894
00:56:03,734 --> 00:56:05,486
Where's Mr. Song?

895
00:56:05,570 --> 00:56:06,696
Oh, Mr. Song?

896
00:56:06,779 --> 00:56:09,949
He must be at the office.
He's the CEO, so...

897
00:56:10,032 --> 00:56:11,659
No.

898
00:56:12,118 --> 00:56:13,494
He went home.

899
00:56:14,328 --> 00:56:16,330
He went home, not to his office?

900
00:56:16,414 --> 00:56:18,291
Yeah, I'm sure he went home.

901
00:56:20,418 --> 00:56:22,879
Sae-byeok, I'll visit you at HOME soon.

902
00:56:22,962 --> 00:56:23,963
See you then.

903
00:56:24,046 --> 00:56:25,673
- Please take good care of her.
- Okay.

904
00:56:25,756 --> 00:56:26,924
- I'll text you.
- Bye.

905
00:56:27,008 --> 00:56:28,009
Goodnight.

906
00:56:34,974 --> 00:56:35,975
Thank you.

907
00:58:01,102 --> 00:58:02,603
I'll wait for you.

908
00:58:02,979 --> 00:58:05,690
I'm really good at waiting
once I set my mind to it.

909
00:58:07,608 --> 00:58:08,693
No way...

910
00:58:16,909 --> 00:58:20,746
SONGI SPICY CHICKEN FEET

911
00:58:39,390 --> 00:58:40,433
What are you doing?

912
00:58:51,777 --> 00:58:52,778
Ui-yeong.

913
00:58:55,614 --> 00:58:56,657
Yes!

914
00:59:01,203 --> 00:59:03,372
Do you want to go on a date
once the project's over?

915
00:59:03,539 --> 00:59:04,540
A date?

916
00:59:05,416 --> 00:59:07,209
I couldn't stop thinking about you,
so here I am.

917
00:59:11,839 --> 00:59:13,174
I like you.

918
00:59:13,674 --> 00:59:16,093
I'm glad we met now.

919
00:59:18,596 --> 00:59:20,306
But don't hesitate to run to me

920
00:59:21,932 --> 00:59:23,350
once your mind's made up.

921
01:00:21,408 --> 01:00:22,660
Is this a dream?

922
01:00:26,497 --> 01:00:29,375
No, it's not.

923
01:00:33,462 --> 01:00:34,505
You're here.

924
01:00:37,133 --> 01:00:38,592
Were you here the whole time?

925
01:00:39,510 --> 01:00:41,178
I couldn't even reach you on the phone.

926
01:00:42,930 --> 01:00:44,890
I know it's warm

927
01:00:45,891 --> 01:00:47,643
but you can't sleep out here.

928
01:00:48,227 --> 01:00:51,647
I took a nap in my car,
but everyone was gone when I came back.

929
01:00:52,773 --> 01:00:55,609
I didn't want you to come
and see that everyone was gone.

930
01:00:56,986 --> 01:00:58,779
And what if I hadn't come?

931
01:01:00,072 --> 01:01:01,490
But you said you'd come.

932
01:01:02,199 --> 01:01:04,285
That was why I waited.

933
01:01:07,705 --> 01:01:10,749
Do you realize...

934
01:01:12,334 --> 01:01:15,421
how heavy of a promise it is
to wait for someone?

935
01:01:23,220 --> 01:01:24,430
Give me a sec.

936
01:01:33,731 --> 01:01:34,732
Huh?

937
01:01:37,943 --> 01:01:39,403
You should just have some water.

938
01:01:44,909 --> 01:01:46,202
You want me to drink with you?

939
01:01:48,204 --> 01:01:49,246
No.

940
01:01:51,332 --> 01:01:54,168
I just need some courage.

941
01:01:54,919 --> 01:01:57,254
And you can't forget

942
01:01:58,672 --> 01:02:01,592
what I'm about to say right now.

943
01:02:15,981 --> 01:02:16,982
I...

944
01:02:18,692 --> 01:02:20,444
didn't come here for the party.

945
01:02:23,530 --> 01:02:26,867
Remember how you told me

946
01:02:29,828 --> 01:02:32,081
to run to you

947
01:02:33,374 --> 01:02:36,460
as soon as my mind was made up?

948
01:02:38,629 --> 01:02:39,797
That was why I came here.

949
01:02:42,258 --> 01:02:44,969
To tell you I've made up my mind.

950
01:02:52,768 --> 01:02:53,936
I like you.

951
01:02:57,982 --> 01:02:58,983
I...

952
01:03:00,943 --> 01:03:02,027
like you

953
01:03:03,279 --> 01:03:04,321
too.

954
01:03:09,118 --> 01:03:10,411
I wanted to see you

955
01:03:12,621 --> 01:03:13,831
and I couldn't hold it back

956
01:03:15,749 --> 01:03:17,042
so here I am.

957
01:03:29,555 --> 01:03:30,681
Thanks for coming.

958
01:03:36,979 --> 01:03:37,980
Promise me

959
01:03:40,190 --> 01:03:41,275
you won't go anywhere.

960
01:04:31,992 --> 01:04:35,537
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

961
01:04:35,829 --> 01:04:40,209
I'LL WAIT FOR YOU

962
01:04:44,338 --> 01:04:47,841
I'VE NEVER FELT THIS WAY BEFORE

963
01:04:47,925 --> 01:04:51,428
THE MOMENT YOU BECOME SURE OF YOUR LOVE

964
01:05:01,563 --> 01:05:04,983
I LIKE YOU

965
01:05:08,779 --> 01:05:09,780
- Ta-da!
- Hm?

966
01:05:10,114 --> 01:05:12,199
Congratulations on your new relationship.

967
01:05:12,616 --> 01:05:14,827
Yeah, anything's possible.

968
01:05:15,953 --> 01:05:17,454
Boyfriend?

969
01:05:17,913 --> 01:05:20,541
We can't just assume
people on dating apps are less serious.

970
01:05:20,624 --> 01:05:22,584
You know how many weirdos go
on blind dates?

971
01:05:22,668 --> 01:05:24,628
So, how many blind dates have you been on?

972
01:05:24,711 --> 01:05:25,754
Just a few.

973
01:05:25,838 --> 01:05:28,966
So, you're the one who got hired
because of Jeong-a.

974
01:05:29,633 --> 01:05:30,926
- Where are you going?
- No way.

975
01:05:31,343 --> 01:05:32,469
- A blind date?
- A blind date?

976
01:05:32,970 --> 01:05:34,096
Let go!

977
01:05:35,180 --> 01:05:36,265
Tae-seop!

978
01:05:43,939 --> 01:05:45,941
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
